<h1>About</h1>
<p style="font-size: 20px">
  <img id="about1" src="images/about/about1.jpg" width="350px" style="border-radius: 20px;float: right; padding: 10px; padding-top: 0px"/> Ross School is rural school catering for Years 1-6 students in two multi-levelled classes. Our school fosters a caring, fun-loving, family atmosphere with the school at the heart of the community.<br /><br />
  The school boasts a full calendar of events, including Pet Day, inter-school swimming sports, concerts, cross country running, and Duffy assemblies.<br /><br /> A well-resourced library is available for students and the community. The school is well supplied with ICT resources and students may bring own devices if they wish. <br /><br />
  <img id="about2"src="images/about/about2.jpg" width="300px" style="border-radius: 20px;float: left; padding: 10px" />Attractive grounds include a sports field, adventure playground, swings, a netball/tennis court and sandpit. A large, covered community swimming pool is situated adjacent to the school and used by students and the community.<br /> <br />
  The school owns and operates a daily bus service to transport students to and from school as well as to enhance learning outside of the classroom.<br /><br />
  Ross School contributes to Westland High School in Hokitika and South Westland Area School in Harihari.
</p>
